WEBVTT

00:15:26.545 --> 00:15:31.786
Once you draw the link between
human flourishing and morality,

00:15:31.810 --> 00:15:35.231
which, I think, the link is very direct,
and we can talk about that,

00:15:35.255 --> 00:15:37.470
but once you draw that link,

00:15:37.494 --> 00:15:40.090
to say there are no right
and wrong answers here

00:15:40.114 --> 00:15:43.821
is tantamount to saying, "We will never
know anything about human well-being.

00:15:43.845 --> 00:15:48.266
There will be no human psychology
that can tell us how people flourish.

00:15:48.290 --> 00:15:50.885
There will be no sociology.
There will be no economics.

00:15:50.909 --> 00:15:54.727
There will be no other discipline
that can give us right and wrong answers."

00:15:54.751 --> 00:15:56.907
And that, I think, is wrong.

00:15:56.931 --> 00:15:59.135
CA: So what you're saying

00:15:59.159 --> 00:16:04.217
is that the root from science
to morality, as it were --